---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';

const updated = 'July 16, 2026';
---

<Base
  title="SMS Terms & Conditions | Speedy Gonzalez Roofing"
  description="Terms for text messages from Speedy Gonzalez Roofing. Message and data rates may apply. Reply STOP to opt out."
  path="/sms-terms"
  breadcrumbs={[{ href: '/sms-terms', label: 'SMS Terms' }]}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h1>SMS Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="lede">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <h2>What you are agreeing to</h2>
      <p>
        When you give {business.name} your mobile number, you agree we may text you about your
        roof. That means estimates, scheduling, job updates, and answers to what you asked.
      </p>

      <h2>How often will you text me?</h2>
      <p>
        Only as often as your job needs. There is no set number. Most of it happens while your
        estimate or your job is active.
      </p>

      <h2>Does it cost anything?</h2>
      <p>
        We do not charge for texts. Your carrier might. Message and data rates may apply,
        depending on your plan.
      </p>

      <h2>How do I stop the texts?</h2>
      <p>
        Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message. We will stop, and you will get one message
        confirming it. If you want them back, reply <strong>START</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>How do I get help?</h2>
      <p>
        Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message, or call {business.phones.office}. A person
        here will pick it up.
      </p>

      <h2>Which carriers are supported?</h2>
      <p>
        Most major US carriers. Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
      </p>

      <h2>Your privacy</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your number. We do not share it for anyone else's marketing. See our{' '}
        <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a> for the full picture.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact us</h2>
      <address>
        {business.name}<br />
        {business.address.street}<br />
        {business.address.city}, {business.address.state} {business.address.zip}<br />
        {business.phones.office}<br />
        <a href={`mailto:${business.email}`}>{business.email}</a>
      </address>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .narrow {
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  address {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>
